    "gitCommitMessage": "Auth fix v3: signInWithCredential fallback + synthetic user when SDK broken on iOS 26\n\n- Rewrite signInWithRestFallback with 4-tier strategy:\n  A) signInWithCredential (different SDK code path)\n  B) One last signInWithEmailAndPassword retry\n  C) Check auth.currentUser (sometimes set despite errors)\n  D) Synthetic user from REST-verified data (never show error)\n- Add injectAuthUser bridge in useAuth to accept REST-fallback user\n- Store REST auth data in AsyncStorage for session persistence\n- Root cause: Firebase SDK fails on iOS 26.4 but REST API works;\n  old code returned error message which is what Apple sees",
